In a small saucepan, combine the stock and salt and bring to a boil over high heat. Remove from the heat and set aside, covered. In a medium saucepan, melt the butter over medium heat. Add the onion and sauté until soft, 1 to 2 minutes. Add the curry powder and sauté 30 seconds. Add the couscous and stir to coat. Add the hot stock, remove from the heat, and let sit 6 to 8 minutes, until absorbed by the couscous, Stir and season with salt and pepper, if needed.